    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-01-01T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-01-01T23:00:00-05:00" n="406"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d406">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/772: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-01-02T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 2, 1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received January 2—6:22
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2. My 1206, December 31, 10 a.m. Following from American Consul at Harbin: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>
                            <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“December 31, 10 a.m. Tsai and Soviet party arrived Harbin this
                                    morning from Changchun. They were met by a few Chinese but many
                                    Soviet adherents waving red flags. Local press reports that Mo
                                    Te-hui has been appointed <hi rend="italic">Tupan</hi> of
                                    Chinese Eastern Railway.”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>
                            <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“December 31, 4 p.m. Soviet prisoners, including those arrested
                                    at Soviet Consulate General May last, liberated today. Meeting
                                    of new board of directors of railway took place at 2 p.m. and
                                    new Soviet General Manager Rudy and Assistant Manager Denisoff
                                    took over chargé of administration of railway at 3:10 p.m.
                                    today.”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
